answers.body_markdown:
your `axios.post(...).then(...)` calls `setState` without `comments`. setter for `useState` does not merge object as it happens in class components but replace value completely.

So after clicking button -&gt; running `postComment ` you are ending up with

```
.then(() =&gt; {
  setState({
    username: &quot;&quot;,
    newComment: &quot;&quot;,
    color: &quot;&quot;,
    date: moment().format(&quot;MMMM Do YYYY h:mm:ss a&quot;)
});
```
And sure, after re-render your `comments` is `undefined`.

The easiest way to handle that is splitting state into several independent variables like

```
const [formData, setFormData] = useState({
  username: &#39;&#39;,
  date: &#39;&#39;,
  color: &quot;#ffff80&quot;,
  newComment: &#39;&#39;
});
const [allComments, setAllComments] = useState([]);
```
So they will not interfere with each other.

